In [30]:
wickets=df_deliveries.dropna(subset=['dismissal_kind'])
wickets=wickets[~wickets['dismissal_kind'].isin(['run out','retired hurt','obstructing the field'])]
wickets_taken=wickets.groupby('bowler')['dismissal_kind'].agg(['count']).reset_index().sort_values('count',ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
wickets_taken.columns=['Bowler Name', 'Wickets Taken']
top15_wicket_takers=wickets_taken.iloc[:15].plot('Bowler Name', 'Wickets Taken',kind='bar',color='Violet')
mpl.title("Top 15 Wicket Takers",fontsize=20)
mpl.xticks(rotation=90)
mpl.xlabel("Player Name",fontsize=15)
mpl.ylabel("Wickets Taken",fontsize=15)
mpl.show()

Results and Conclusions¶

Leading Run Scorer in IPL¶

  • Virat Kohli is the leading run scorer in the history of IPL.
  • David Warner is the highest run getter amongst all foreign players.

Leading Wicket-taker in IPL¶

  • Lasith Malinga is the leading wicket-taker in the history of IPL.
  • Amit Mishra is tops the list of wicket-takers among Indian players.

Most sixes in IPL¶

  • Chris Gayle tops the list of most number of sixes through the tournament with a huge margin against the second-placed AB de Villiers.
  • MS Dhoni is the leading six-hitter among Indian players.

Most fours in IPL¶

  • Shikhar Dhawan has hit most number of fours through the years, marginally surpassing Suresh Raina.
  • David Warner tops the list of most number of fours hit among all the foreign players.

Most successful franchise in IPL¶

  • Mumbai Indians is the most successful franchise in the history of IPL winning 4 IPL titles followed by the 3 titles won by Chennai Super Kings.
  • Royal Challengers Bangalore, Kings XI Punjab and Delhi Capitals have not won a single title.

Most number of matches won in the tournament¶

  • Mumbai Indians, Chennai Super Kings and Kolkata Knight Riders have won most number of matches in the history of the tournament.

Most player of the match awards¶

  • Chris Gayle has won most number of man of the match awards, closely followed by AB de Villiers.

Most common mode of dismissal in IPL¶

  • Most players in the tournament have been dismissed caught in the field.
  • No player has ever been dismissed obstructing the field in the history of the tournament.

Most number of matches played¶

  • Suresh Raina has played most number of matches in the history of the tournament, followed by Rohit Sharma and Robin Uthappa.
  • Shane Watson has made most appearances among foreign players.

Scoring trend over the years¶

  • Over the years, players have been more dependent on scoring through big hits, reducing the difference between number of fours and sixes hit through the season.

Toss dependency in league matches¶

  • There has been a growing trend over the years, where the teams chasing have gone onto win the matches.

Toss dependency in IPL finals¶

  • 9 out of 11 finals have seen the winner of the toss going on to win the final as well.

Toss Choices in league matches¶

  • 61.2% of teams have elected to field first throughout the tournament, compared to 38.2%, where the teams have elected to bat first.
  • Over the years, there has been a trend where the teams have elected to chase and gone onto win the match.

Toss Choices in IPL Finals¶

  • 58.3% of teams have elected to bat first in IPL finals, compared to 41.7% of teams electing to field first.

Match Result based on toss¶

  • 55.4% of teams have won the match bowling first, while 44.6% of teams have won batting first.

Matches played through the seasons¶

  • There has been a significant consistency in the number of matches played in each season, barring the 2012, 2013 and 2014 seasons.
